messages.text: I don't think I can do this, Aaron.
They will be fine.
They'll get some sleep and wake up in the morning.
it just feels creepy... and risky
After all we've been through...you can't back out now.
Remember the pledge we made?
Can't you once think about what I'M going thru?!
I know it's difficult for you
YOU DON'T KNOW!
I love you & I want us to be together and to stop my folks from keeping us apart
but I'm not going to do this to them... I can't.
what if I overdose them and they fall into a coma?
or die???
That won't happen if you just give them each the normal dose & all at the same time.
You don't understand!!
One day they'll want to see their grandkids.
I can't take that away from them
You're right. I'm being insensitive.
But Eva, keep thinking about the future.
They will want to see our children. We will welcome them into our home...
And once they see the kids' faces - hold them in their arms...
feel the warmth of their bodies...
listen to their hearts beating faster than a butterfly's wings...
They will forgive you.
And you them.
But if we don't take the next step to be together...
none of that will happen. Ever.
I'm thinking how much I fight with them
but I still love them.
meanwhile you and i never fight
and i'm afraid of losing your love if we start
So this isn't really about your folks.
You're afraid to take the next step...
because you realize this time it's for real.
I'm scared too.
It's safer not to take that leap into the unknown.
Not to risk failure, or pain.
But if we don't leap, we may never know how good it could have been...
Aaron...
Yes?
Stop being so right.
Just promise me we won't become like them.
You have my word.
i'm still scared...
You said they got you working in the kitchen, right?
So...mix the pills inside their dinner.
You can monitor their sleep and let me know if they have any trouble.
I'll be standing by in my friend's car to take you wherever you need to go.
The hospital's less than 5 minutes away. No need to worry.
ok gimme some time... I'll text you after dinner.
a little bit later
Unbelievable!
What?
They fell asleep before dessert - and now snoring like thunder!
You feeling ok about it?
totally amped!
b out soon...
a little bit later
Eva - STAY INSIDE!
DON'T COME OUT!!!
What happened?
there are gangs roaming the streets
stopping cars & hijacking them
taking over houses
Is our house ok?
afraid not.
6 guys inside it now - with guns
NO!
I'm gonna try to smoke them out -
give you enough time to escape and jump in the car with me.
DON'T. IT'S TOO DANGEROUS!
Just stand by the hatch, ready to open it. I'll be nearby...
AARON NO!!!
a little bit later
NOW, EVA! COME OUT NOW!
one hour later
You ok in there?
yeah... be back out soon...
It's crazy how empty this gas station is.
No one in the ladies room either.
You were shaking pretty bad.
just putting more cold water on my face. no worries...
very proud how you spoofed that gang out of my house.
All it took was a flare - attracted them like moths to a flame
funny... do you smell smoke?
Hold on...
I see a forest fire behind the station. Come out now!
two days later
Eva and Aaron's group chat
Anyone out there??
We're sending this to all of our contacts.
If you get this please reply.
Two days ago we were running from a forest fire...
and we took refuge in Forest Lawn Cemetery inside a mausoleum.
We were shocked and scared when we finally went outside...
and saw the devastation of every tree and blade of grass.
When we drove through downtown...there was no one in sight...
not one bird or animal.
We're in search of supplies - and people.
Hope we can find the courage to continue alone.
Our love can protect us only so far...
Please - someone...
Let us know we are not the only ones left behind...
THE END
